{{Quote|City was being lived in by my own people! Yes! Was great majesty, and wonderful comfort. But then, one day city die! Bombs fall from ships flown by people called 'Empire', yes? No reason then – no reason now. But bombs turn city to ruins, and turn my people to homeless nomads.|G'hinji Dros|<ref name="marvel62" />}}
'''Chinshassa''' was a [[City/Legends|city]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Shalyvane]], which was destroyed by an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] bombardment during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="marvel62" /> A holy city for the Em'liy<ref name="sanbra">{{GamerCite|1|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Marvel Series}}</ref> located close to the venerated site known as the [[Circle of Kavaan/Legends|Circle of Kavaan]], Chinshassa was suddenly annihilated by the Imperials as part of an operation aimed at the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]]&mdash;in order to establish cover for an Imperial agent named [[Lumiya|Shira Brie]] to infiltrate the Rebels, they gave Brie the backstory that she was a war refugee from Chinshassa after it had been destroyed by Em'liy aggressors.<ref name="marvel62" />

Although the Em'liy were aware of this deception, they took the destruction of Chinshassa as a great, personal shame, and avoided the city for many years.<ref name="sanbra" /> Brie further reinforced this cover with a visit to Chinshassa along with several Rebel [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]], where they engaged in a firefight with vengeful Em'liy. Some time later, Rebel [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] visited Chinshassa to further research Brie after apparently killing her in a friendly fire incident. There, a [[G'hinji Dros|surviving native]] set the record straight, revealing the true history of Chinshassa's destruction.<ref name="marvel62" />

